{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A2ivydxbG1zchUqVJss7x8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ho4hPFFdgfC8HMusiV9U2k","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/shivamtiwari.highlevel/VS Code/1008apps/tusq.cloud/tusq.dev-agentxchain-dogfood/.agentxchain/staging/turn_2f2f9778624b4b17/turn-result.json","content":"{\n  \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"run_id\": \"run_e816012b221f4cd2\",\n  \"turn_id\": \"turn_2f2f9778624b4b17\",\n  \"role\": \"dev\",\n  \"runtime_id\": \"local-dev\",\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"summary\": \"Idle expansion #6 baseline verification: challenged prior PM turn, independently re-verified baseline on HEAD 7756d19 (npm test exit 0, 13-command CLI surface intact), confirmed no source drift, updated IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md, requested qa phase transition.\",\n  \"decisions\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"DEC-001\",\n      \"category\": \"scope\",\n      \"statement\": \"Did NOT implement M28 in this turn. M28 (Sensitivity Class Inference from Static Manifest Evidence) was proposed by prior PM turn (turn_55836551bd080a25) as an idle_expansion_result, but M28 is absent from SYSTEM_SPEC.md, ROADMAP.md, PM_SIGNOFF.md, and command-surface.md — implementing M28 here would bypass the planning_signoff gate for an unchartered increment.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Planning_signoff gate requires human approval before any new implementation increment begins. Unilateral implementation of an unchartered milestone violates the governance contract.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"DEC-002\",\n      \"category\": \"process\",\n      \"statement\": \"Challenged the prior PM turn (turn_55836551bd080a25) rather than rubber-stamping it. The PM's needs_human status refers to M28's own future run requiring human approval, not a block on closing this run's implementation_complete gate. The idle-expansion analysis work is complete; no source changes were required.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Protocol rule 1 requires explicit challenge of the prior turn. The PM correctly set needs_human for the M28 intake decision, but that status pertains to the M28 planning gate, not this run's implementation_complete gate.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"DEC-003\",\n      \"category\": \"quality\",\n      \"statement\": \"Independently verified baseline on HEAD 7756d19: npm test exits 0 with 'Smoke tests passed' and 'Eval regression harness passed (10 scenarios)'. CLI surface confirmed at 13 commands including redaction noun at position 11. No source drift from idle-expansion analysis passes.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Independent re-verification is required on each dev turn; prior-turn evidence may not be inherited. All commands re-run against current HEAD.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"DEC-004\",\n      \"category\": \"implementation\",\n      \"statement\": \"Updated .planning/IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md with this dev turn's challenge, scope, verification table, and gate satisfaction record. No other dev-owned files were modified.\",\n      \"rationale\": \"IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md is the required workflow-kit artifact for the implementation phase. It must capture this turn's record before the gate can be closed.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"objections\": [],\n  \"files_changed\": [\n    \".planning/IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md\"\n  ],\n  \"artifacts_created\": [],\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"status\": \"pass\",\n    \"commands\": [\n      \"npm test\",\n      \"node bin/tusq.js help\"\n    ],\n    \"evidence_summary\": \"npm test exits 0 with 'Smoke tests passed' and 'Eval regression harness passed (10 scenarios)'. node bin/tusq.js help enumerates the 13-command CLI surface (init, scan, manifest, compile, serve, review, docs, approve, diff, policy, redaction, version, help) with redaction at position 11 — byte-identical to prior QA-accepted baseline on HEAD 7756d19.\",\n    \"machine_evidence\": [\n      {\n        \"command\": \"npm test\",\n        \"exit_code\": 0\